DISCLOSURE_INFO:
{
  "Initiated By" : "AMERICAN STOCK EXCHANGE",
  "Description of Investigation" : "U5 DISCLOSES A VOLUNTARY TERMINATION ON 7/2/81 WITH ITEM 13C MARKED \"YES\". PELTON IS CURRENTLY THE SUBJECT OF AN AMERICAN STOCK EXCHANGE INVESTIGATION WHICH WAS PROMPTED BY A CUSTOMER COMPLAINT. THE COMPLAINT ALLEGES PELTON OPENED AN OPTIONS ACCOUNT FOR A MR. QUINTON BUCKLEY ON 2/17/80. THE CLIENTS INFORMED PELTON THAT THEY HAD APPROX. $15,000 AVAILABLE TO THEM FOR 60 DAYS, AT WHICH TIME THEY NEEDED THE MONEY FOR AN IRS DEBT. THEY CLAIM PELTON ADVISED THEM THAT OPTIONS WOULD BE THEIR BEST INVESTMENT WITHOUT RISKING ANY CAPITAL. PELTON DENIES THAT THE CLIENTS EVER MENTIONED ANYTHING ABOUT AN IRS DEBT. HE ALSO STATED THAT HE INFORMED THEM OF THE RISKS INVOLVED WITH OPTIONS AND THAT THEY WILLINGLY SIGNED THE OPTIONS AGREEMENT. THE BUCKLEY'S ARE NOW TRYING TO RECOVER THE INVESTMENT THAT WAS LOST WHEN THE OPTION EXPIRED WORTHLESS. THE SUIT WAS SETTLED OUT OF COURT."
}
